The muscle lettered B is innervated by: <image 1> 

A. Cranial Nerve III.
B. Cranial Nerve IV.
C. Cranial Nerve VI.

The muscle labeled as B in the image is the Superior Oblique muscle of the eye. The Superior Oblique muscle is innervated by Cranial Nerve IV, also known as the Trochlear Nerve.

So, the correct answer is:
B. Cranial Nerve IV.
